<div id="review_1041280178" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1041280178" />
    <a title="Vannessa Anderson" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1380029-vannessa-anderson"><img alt="Vannessa Anderson" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1442485967p2/1380029.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1041280178?book_show_action=true">Aug 31, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Vannessa Anderson" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Vannessa Anderson" href="/user/show/1380029-vannessa-anderson">Vannessa Anderson</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1380029-vannessa-anderson?shelf=science-medicine-research-techno">science-medicine-research-techno</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1380029-vannessa-anderson?shelf=nonfiction">nonfiction</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1041280178" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4366517466833602659"><u>From the book</u><br/><br/><i>
  <b> Dr. James Marion Sims invented eponymous gynecological instruments used for surgeries upon black female slaves in the 1840s. Each naked, unanesthetized slave woman had to be forcibly restrained by the other physicians though her shrieks of agony as Sims determinedly, sliced, then sutured her genitalia.<br/><br/>Many studies enrolled only or principally African Americas some included a smattering of Hispanics.<br/><br/>Tuskegee Syphilis Study in 1970s to 1996.<br/><br/>Jailing of poor black mothers who were u</b></i></span>
  <span id="freeText4366517466833602659" style="display:none"><u>From the book</u><br /><br /><i>
  <b> Dr. James Marion Sims invented eponymous gynecological instruments used for surgeries upon black female slaves in the 1840s. Each naked, unanesthetized slave woman had to be forcibly restrained by the other physicians though her shrieks of agony as Sims determinedly, sliced, then sutured her genitalia.<br /><br />Many studies enrolled only or principally African Americas some included a smattering of Hispanics.<br /><br />Tuskegee Syphilis Study in 1970s to 1996.<br /><br />Jailing of poor black mothers who were unwitting research subjects in South Carolina.<br /><br />1998 infusion of poor black New York City boys with the cardio toxic drug fenfluramine.<br /><br />It was cheaper to use Niggers than cats because they were everywhere and cheap experimental animals—neurosurgeon Harry Bailey, M.D.<br /><br />The future of the Negro lies more in the research laboratory than in schools…. When diseased, he should be registered and forced to take treatment before he offers his diseased mind and body on the altar of academic and professional education—Thomas Murrell<b></b></b>
</i><br /><br />The above is just a preview of what you’re going to learn in <i>Medical Apartheid</i>. I thought I’d be angry after reading <i>Medical Apartheid</i> but I reminded myself that these individuals were born of males and females who produced defective sperm and defective egg that produced defected children (sociopaths, psychopaths and narcissists).<br /><br />Learning the definitions of racism, racialism and racialist were enlightening. After reading <i>Medical Apartheid</i>, what came to mine was Nazi scientists and ISIS. I am reminded that Nazi scientists were recruited by American companies: <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="http://www.angelfire.com/ca3/jphuck/BOOK3Ch2.html">http://www.angelfire.com/ca3/jphuck/B...</a>, <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="http://information4sale.blogspot.com/2011/07/project-paperclip-recruitment-of-nazi.html">http://information4sale.blogspot.com/...</a>, <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="http://www.naturalnews.com/036484_Bayer_Nazi_war_crimes.html">http://www.naturalnews.com/036484_Bay...</a>.<br /><br /><i>Medical Apartheid</i> was just one of many holocaust atrocities committed on Americans of African descent and is not only an important read but a necessary read. <br /><br /><i>Medical Apartheid</i> is a reference of History that should never be forgotten.<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="4366517466833602659" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


